WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.476
What's after
high school, Brian?

00:03.762 --> 00:06.340
Me and Mack Brown gonna
get our win on in Pasadena.

00:06.381 --> 00:07.633
Get my national
championship on,

00:07.674 --> 00:09.510
and my Heisman on.

00:09.510 --> 00:10.969
Do you have anyone
you're interested in?

00:11.011 --> 00:12.304
Sorta.
Sorta?

00:12.346 --> 00:14.097
Well, forget about sorta.
You know what?

00:14.139 --> 00:15.098
Take her out.

00:15.140 --> 00:16.183
Movies, dinner.

00:16.183 --> 00:17.017
Get her in the back seat
of your car.

00:17.059 --> 00:18.519
I don't care.
Whatever.

00:18.519 --> 00:19.853
I love you.

00:19.895 --> 00:22.064
I love you too.

00:23.899 --> 00:25.359
What do you want
to talk about, Tim?

00:25.359 --> 00:27.444
That fact that
you're sleeping with

00:27.486 --> 00:29.029
your paralyzed
best friend's girlfriend?

00:29.029 --> 00:31.281
The three of us together

00:31.323 --> 00:33.951
can get through anything.

00:33.992 --> 00:34.993
Anything at all.

00:50.926 --> 00:53.971
[cheering]

00:56.056 --> 00:57.432
Whoops.

01:00.102 --> 01:02.562
Waste of friggin' time, huh?

01:02.562 --> 01:05.190
Look, I know
you hate me right now,

01:05.232 --> 01:07.025
and I understand.
I don't hate you, Lyla.

01:08.402 --> 01:09.945
It'd be a lot easier
if I did.

01:12.030 --> 01:13.156
I don't know how
to talk to you

01:13.198 --> 01:14.741
when you're like this.

01:14.741 --> 01:16.201
I mean, God,
it's not even 7:00,

01:16.243 --> 01:20.122
and you can barely stand.

01:20.122 --> 01:22.457
You can blame me
if you want, Tim.

01:22.457 --> 01:23.625
You can blame
the whole world,

01:23.667 --> 01:24.918
for all I care.

01:24.960 --> 01:26.712
But if you think
being drunk all the time

01:26.753 --> 01:28.255
is gonna make this
any easier,

01:28.297 --> 01:29.715
you're wrong.

01:29.756 --> 01:32.175
It's not cool
or charming.

01:32.217 --> 01:35.387
It's just pathetic
and gross.

01:35.429 --> 01:36.722
And I feel sorry
for you.

01:36.763 --> 01:39.099
I really do.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.143
Lyla.

01:42.769 --> 01:46.565
(Mayor Rodell)
Didn't this 2000
championship team

01:46.606 --> 01:49.276
have a...star quarterback?

01:49.276 --> 01:51.361
[cheering]

01:51.403 --> 01:52.571
Do y'all remember?

01:52.612 --> 01:54.239
Hmm?

01:54.281 --> 01:57.200
I said, do you remember?

01:57.242 --> 02:00.120
[cheering]

02:00.120 --> 02:02.831
[marching band drumming]

02:02.831 --> 02:05.167
[taped announcer over P. A.]
Six seconds to go,

02:05.208 --> 02:07.753
the Panthers lining up
for a field goal.

02:07.794 --> 02:10.255
Mize takes the snap,
he fields it clean.

02:10.297 --> 02:12.299
Wait a second, it's a fake!

02:12.299 --> 02:14.551
Alpert's open.
He's got Alpert!

02:14.593 --> 02:16.720
Mize rolling right, throws.

02:16.762 --> 02:17.763
He caught it!

02:17.804 --> 02:20.474
Robbie Alpert caught
the dadgum ball!

02:20.474 --> 02:23.602
Panthers win State!
Panthers win State!

02:23.644 --> 02:25.812
[cheering]

02:25.812 --> 02:31.568
(Mayor Rodell)
Ladies and gentlemen,
All‐Region, All‐District,

02:31.610 --> 02:33.820
All‐State‐‐

02:33.820 --> 02:36.156
Lucas "The Maneater" Mize.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.784
[cheering]

02:38.825 --> 02:41.828
[crowd chanting]
Lucas Mize! Lucas Mize!

02:41.828 --> 02:43.538
Lucas Mize!

02:43.538 --> 02:45.540
Lucas Mize!

02:45.540 --> 02:48.835
You know, that's gonna
be you one day, Brian.

02:48.835 --> 02:51.088
Maybe so, little sis.

02:51.129 --> 02:53.256
Maybe so.

02:53.298 --> 02:56.259
[country rock music playing]

02:56.301 --> 03:04.393
♪ ♪

03:17.864 --> 03:20.033
Hey, I'm Lucas Mize.
Brian.

03:20.075 --> 03:22.369
But everybody around here
calls me Smash.

03:22.411 --> 03:24.287
Smash.
Smash, huh?

03:24.329 --> 03:25.330
Did you come up
with that one on your own?

03:25.372 --> 03:29.209
Yeah, well,
Maneater was taken.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.210
Oh, yeah.

03:30.252 --> 03:32.504
Who was that, anyway?
The Carpenters or something?

03:32.546 --> 03:33.547
Who was that?

03:33.547 --> 03:37.634
This guy used to drive
22 miles from Macedonia

03:37.676 --> 03:39.302
every day
of my sophomore year,

03:39.344 --> 03:40.846
just to work me out
in private.

03:40.887 --> 03:41.638
I needed the money.

03:41.680 --> 03:43.348
(Tami)
So, how are you?

03:43.390 --> 03:44.391
How's your family?
What's been going on?

03:44.433 --> 03:45.267
I'm selling insurance.

03:45.308 --> 03:47.185
I have an insurance agency
in Dallas.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.062
In Dallas?
I've got a sister in Plano.

03:49.104 --> 03:49.938
You got a card?
I'll give it to her.

03:49.980 --> 03:52.065
I did, but there's
so many people here.

03:52.107 --> 03:53.692
I've been giving them out.
Like this guy.

03:53.733 --> 03:56.153
This guy here is one
of the best running backs

03:56.194 --> 03:57.571
in the state of Texas,
when he's listening.

03:57.612 --> 03:59.239
Which is very rare.
Come on, Coach.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.408
But when he's listening,
he's a hell of a running back.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.367
Is that right?

04:02.409 --> 04:04.578
Well, you must be feeling
the pressure, then.

04:04.578 --> 04:06.872
All the alums back,
big homecoming game.

04:06.913 --> 04:08.290
Oh, I‐‐

04:08.290 --> 04:09.291
Grady Hunt in the house.

04:09.291 --> 04:10.625
Who?

04:10.625 --> 04:11.877
You haven't met him yet?

04:11.918 --> 04:12.752
Come on, Coach.

04:12.794 --> 04:15.255
You gotta take care
of your boy here.

04:15.297 --> 04:19.384
Come with me, kid.

04:19.426 --> 04:20.385
Take care, Lucas.

04:20.427 --> 04:21.303
Nice to see you, Lucas.

04:21.344 --> 04:22.429
Good to see you,
Mrs. Taylor.

04:22.429 --> 04:23.597
Okay.

04:23.597 --> 04:25.599
Mr. Hunt's been scouting
high school ball

04:25.599 --> 04:27.100
since before
we were born.

04:27.142 --> 04:28.602
He knows all
the recruiters.

04:28.602 --> 04:31.104
You make his top 100 list,
you're good to go.

04:31.146 --> 04:32.272
He's the man.

04:32.272 --> 04:34.608
Lucas.
How are you, man?

04:34.608 --> 04:35.734
Doing good.
Good to see you.

04:35.776 --> 04:36.735
Good to see you.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.779
I can bench press 270,

04:38.779 --> 04:41.782
dead lift 450,
and run a 4.3, with pads.

04:41.782 --> 04:44.451
Plus, my vert's 37 inches,
on a bad day.

04:44.451 --> 04:45.869
Last year I got the school
record in points scored,

04:45.911 --> 04:47.788
TD catches,
and total offense.

04:47.829 --> 04:49.998
And the thing about it is,
I'm just a junior.

04:49.998 --> 04:51.500
I ain't even
started yet.

04:51.500 --> 04:53.710
I'm a little worried
about his confidence.

04:53.752 --> 04:54.920
Yeah.

04:54.961 --> 04:56.963
Look, no disrespect, sir.

04:56.963 --> 04:58.590
I just want to say
flat out,

04:58.632 --> 05:02.302
if you got a list,
I don't just want to be on it.

05:02.302 --> 05:03.887
I want to be number one.

05:03.929 --> 05:07.307
Well, I hope you can play
as good as you talk.

05:07.307 --> 05:08.809
Now's your time, son.

05:08.809 --> 05:10.519
Show me what you got.

05:12.521 --> 05:15.273
Thank you.

05:18.777 --> 05:21.738
[heartfelt instrumental music]

05:21.780 --> 05:31.832
♪ ♪

05:31.873 --> 05:41.842
♪ ♪

05:41.842 --> 05:51.810
♪ ♪

06:05.031 --> 06:08.493
Man, who knew
she didn't like sushi?

06:08.535 --> 06:10.954
Everybody likes sushi,
man.

06:10.996 --> 06:13.915
Hey, where are you
right now, man?

06:13.957 --> 06:16.626
I'm confiding in you, bro.

06:16.668 --> 06:18.044
Sorry, sorry.
Sorry.

06:18.044 --> 06:19.379
What, just 'cause
I have stumps,

06:19.379 --> 06:20.463
do I not bleed?

06:20.505 --> 06:21.965
Dude.

06:22.007 --> 06:24.718
All right, so you took her
to Chinese, and‐‐

06:24.759 --> 06:27.846
Dude, I took her
to sushi.

06:27.888 --> 06:31.391
Sorry, man, I just got...
a lot going on.

06:31.391 --> 06:32.225
Hey, guys.

06:32.267 --> 06:33.310
Hey, Coach.

06:33.351 --> 06:34.394
How you doing, bud?
What's up?

06:34.394 --> 06:36.313
This is Corey.

06:36.354 --> 06:37.564
Hey.
Nice to meet you.

06:37.606 --> 06:38.565
I got potato chips
all over my arm.

06:38.607 --> 06:39.733
That's all right.

06:39.733 --> 06:41.401
I'm sorry,
I don't mean to be rude,

06:41.443 --> 06:43.320
Can I get a second
with him?
Sure.

06:43.361 --> 06:45.363
I'll talk to you later.
Very nice to meet you.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.908
Keep that thought, all right?
I'll listen later.

06:47.949 --> 06:48.992
I promise.
Sure.

06:49.034 --> 06:52.078
Thank you.

06:52.078 --> 06:53.371
How you doing?

06:53.413 --> 06:54.372
I'm doing good.
Yeah?

06:54.414 --> 06:55.540
Aren't you supposed
to be at a party right now?

06:55.582 --> 06:57.542
No, I was‐‐

06:57.584 --> 07:01.504
Pudnick tossed up his nachos
during the line dance.

07:01.546 --> 07:02.756
It was a pretty messy
situation.

07:02.797 --> 07:04.507
Did they shut the party down
because of it?

07:04.549 --> 07:06.426
No, but they should have.

07:06.426 --> 07:09.429
Hey, listen...

07:09.429 --> 07:12.891
I'm kind of like
a designated ambassador

07:12.932 --> 07:14.351
from school right now.

07:14.392 --> 07:17.437
And what I'm
asking you is, uh,

07:17.437 --> 07:20.940
how would you like to come out
to the game Friday night?

07:20.940 --> 07:23.777
It's Homecoming.

07:28.490 --> 07:31.451
Uh...I don't know, Coach.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.953
Hey, look, if it's too soon,
or, you know,

07:33.953 --> 07:34.996
you're not comfortable
with it,

07:34.996 --> 07:36.498
I understand.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.833
They really want me there?

07:38.833 --> 07:41.836
Hell, son, we all
want you there.

07:45.799 --> 07:47.967
Do me a favor,
would you?

07:48.009 --> 07:49.427
Just think about it.

07:52.806 --> 07:54.891
(Billy)
Let me tell you,
they made money.

07:54.933 --> 07:56.476
I mean, big money.

07:56.476 --> 07:57.811
They had kegs,
they had girls.

07:57.811 --> 07:59.479
And those college kids
were paying $20 a pop,

07:59.479 --> 08:00.480
just to get
inside the door.

08:00.480 --> 08:01.481
It was out of control.

08:01.481 --> 08:02.941
Now, where was this?

08:02.982 --> 08:04.818
Abilene.
City of opportunity.

08:04.818 --> 08:07.487
And I'm telling you,
it could work here, T.

08:07.487 --> 08:11.491
My buddy made a killing
throwing these parties.

08:11.491 --> 08:12.325
What up, baby sis?

08:12.367 --> 08:15.453
Seriously, Billy,
you still on that?

08:15.495 --> 08:16.830
You're a lot of things,

08:16.830 --> 08:19.165
but party planner,
not one of 'em.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.542
Your sister here
is a small thinker.

08:20.542 --> 08:23.420
Big in other areas,
but small.

08:23.461 --> 08:24.504
It's a dumb idea,
asshat.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.672
In case you haven't noticed,

08:25.672 --> 08:26.756
this isn't exactly
a college town.

08:26.798 --> 08:28.675
But we do have
a high school.

08:28.717 --> 08:30.844
It's Homecoming, everybody's
gonna be at the dance.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.011
You can't fight
tradition, sweetheart.

08:32.011 --> 08:33.012
Not here.

08:33.012 --> 08:34.764
Then we'll start
a new one.

08:34.806 --> 08:36.516
Exactly.
The anti‐Homecoming.

08:36.558 --> 08:37.684
Uh‐huh.

08:37.684 --> 08:38.852
Mm‐hmm.

08:38.852 --> 08:40.854
You gotta go.

08:40.895 --> 08:42.522
You're too young to
be in here, anyway.

08:42.564 --> 08:44.023
Whatever.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.984
Hey, clear eyes,
full hearts, can't lose.

08:48.653 --> 08:50.780
Damn.

08:55.201 --> 08:57.829
Hey, man.

08:57.871 --> 08:59.539
Just saw your girlfriend.

08:59.581 --> 09:03.209
She is one tall drink
of water.

09:03.209 --> 09:05.503
Can't imagine how
you screwed that one up.

09:05.545 --> 09:06.588
Here.

09:09.758 --> 09:11.426
I'm good.

09:12.218 --> 09:13.970
Dude, nightcap.
SportsCenter.

09:14.012 --> 09:16.389
I quit.

09:16.431 --> 09:17.724
You quit?
[scoffs]

09:17.724 --> 09:18.892
Since when?

09:18.892 --> 09:21.061
Since now.

09:21.061 --> 09:22.562
[laughing]

09:22.562 --> 09:25.190
Sure you did.

09:27.525 --> 09:29.235
(Lyla)
We were worried
you might get in trouble

09:29.235 --> 09:30.820
for being out all night.

09:30.862 --> 09:33.698
What are they gonna do,
throw me in rehab jail?

09:33.740 --> 09:36.493
[chuckles]

09:36.534 --> 09:41.956
So, do you and Timmy see a lot
of each other now?

09:41.956 --> 09:43.792
What do you mean?

09:43.792 --> 09:46.544
I don't know, like,
in school,

09:46.586 --> 09:49.589
or in practice,
or around?

09:49.589 --> 09:51.758
No, not really.

09:51.800 --> 09:54.636
Pretty much
the same amount.

10:04.729 --> 10:06.773
I'm so proud of you,
sweetie.

10:06.815 --> 10:08.108
Phil says
you're doing better

10:08.108 --> 10:10.777
than any patient
he's ever had.

10:10.777 --> 10:13.947
[Jason chuckles]
Phil told me yesterday
to put wax in my hair,

10:13.947 --> 10:17.117
so I wouldn't listen
too much

10:17.117 --> 10:19.077
what he says.

10:23.706 --> 10:25.917
Does your neck hurt
like this?

10:25.959 --> 10:27.794
Like I'd tell you
if it did?

10:27.794 --> 10:30.505
Probably not.

10:34.175 --> 10:37.220
(Saracen)
Just stop talking
about Julie already.

10:37.262 --> 10:39.264
(Landry)
You know what?
That's just what I do.

10:39.305 --> 10:43.476
You know, I pry, I prod,
I wheedle.

10:43.518 --> 10:46.146
You know, even when I get
a little crazy sometimes,

10:46.146 --> 10:47.272
I cajole.

10:47.313 --> 10:48.481
Yeah, but mostly
you annoy.

10:48.523 --> 10:49.649
Well, it's as easy
as this.

10:49.649 --> 10:50.900
If you want it to stop,

10:50.942 --> 10:53.653
you ask Julie out
on a date.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.989
What‐‐I'm really starting
to worry about you.

10:55.989 --> 10:58.658
'Cause you've obviously
got the mojo.

10:58.658 --> 11:00.285
But you just don't really
know how to use it.

11:00.326 --> 11:01.828
You know what
I'm talking about?

11:01.828 --> 11:04.706
I really have no idea
what you're talking about.

11:04.747 --> 11:07.625
What you need is to get
the eye of the tiger.

11:07.667 --> 11:09.085
You know what
I'm talking about.

11:09.127 --> 11:10.670
Boom, baby!

11:10.670 --> 11:12.839
[grunting and growling]

11:12.881 --> 11:14.674
(assistant coach)
That's it.

11:14.716 --> 11:16.676
[whistle blows]

11:16.718 --> 11:18.636
Way to work, Riggins!

11:18.678 --> 11:20.180
One, nine!

11:20.180 --> 11:21.681
Left tuck!

11:21.681 --> 11:23.600
Hut!

11:23.641 --> 11:26.644
[hip‐hop music]

11:26.686 --> 11:28.855
♪ ♪

11:28.855 --> 11:30.690
Way to work it, Smash!
Go!

11:30.690 --> 11:31.816
Way to go, Smash!

11:31.858 --> 11:33.193
[whistle blows]

11:33.193 --> 11:34.194
[applause]

11:34.235 --> 11:36.154
Hey, look,
y'all keep trying,

11:36.196 --> 11:37.614
but you ain't gonna
catch me.

11:37.655 --> 11:38.698
You're wrong, Williams.

11:38.740 --> 11:41.159
Hey, don't hate,
accelerate.

11:41.201 --> 11:42.160
[whistle blows]

11:42.202 --> 11:43.703
Bring it in on the half.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.246
Come on.

11:45.246 --> 11:47.582
(Taylor)
All right, listen up now.

11:47.624 --> 11:49.751
The option's just part of what
you're gonna see Friday night.

11:49.751 --> 11:50.627
They're gonna have a man in
motion every play,

11:50.668 --> 11:51.628
multiple sets.

11:51.669 --> 11:52.712
They're gonna come in here,

11:52.712 --> 11:55.715
they're gonna try
to run and shoot.

11:55.757 --> 11:56.674
Let 'em try.
We'll be ready for 'em.

11:56.716 --> 11:59.677
I don't expect y'all
to contain this offense.

11:59.719 --> 12:02.680
I expect you to shut
the damn thing down, understood?

12:02.722 --> 12:03.556
(players)
Yes, sir.

12:03.556 --> 12:04.891
All right, let's do it!
Break it down.

12:04.933 --> 12:06.226
Coach, wait.
Hold up.

12:06.267 --> 12:08.311
Yo, Hall & Oates...

12:08.353 --> 12:10.730
Let's see if you got
any magic left.

12:10.730 --> 12:15.568
[cheers and catcalls]

12:15.610 --> 12:17.612
(Lucas)
Hut!

12:19.239 --> 12:21.741
[cheers and applause]

12:21.741 --> 12:24.661
Yeah.

12:24.702 --> 12:26.204
Hut!

12:29.165 --> 12:30.333
[cheering]

12:32.210 --> 12:35.755
[cheers and applause]

12:35.797 --> 12:37.340
All right, Mr. Smash.

12:37.382 --> 12:39.759
Homie, go deep.

12:39.759 --> 12:40.760
Hey, man, you can't
throw it that far

12:40.802 --> 12:41.928
without your
theme music.

12:41.928 --> 12:43.429
[chuckles]

12:43.429 --> 12:45.306
Hut!
Hut!

12:51.771 --> 12:53.398
[cheering]

12:53.439 --> 12:54.691
Nice hands.

12:54.732 --> 12:55.858
Soft as
a Tijuana hooker.

12:58.403 --> 13:02.699
(Tyra)
All right, I'll call you later.
Bye.

13:02.740 --> 13:05.076
So, what do you think?

13:05.118 --> 13:06.744
[scoffs]

13:06.786 --> 13:09.998
Are you kidding?
There's nothing out here.

13:09.998 --> 13:11.165
Exactly.

13:11.165 --> 13:12.959
So nobody can get
in any trouble.

13:12.959 --> 13:16.713
Yeah, because
nobody's gonna come.

13:16.754 --> 13:17.964
Maybe your sister
was right.

13:17.964 --> 13:20.049
Okay, you need to relax,
Mr. Negative.

13:20.091 --> 13:22.093
That was her
on the phone.

13:22.135 --> 13:23.428
She and her friends are
gonna be here all night.

13:23.469 --> 13:24.971
Paying 'em 50 bucks a head,
plus tips.

13:24.971 --> 13:25.888
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

13:25.930 --> 13:27.807
Wait a minute.
What are you talking about?

13:27.849 --> 13:28.975
Hey, every good party needs
a hostess, Billy,

13:28.975 --> 13:30.143
and we've got ten of 'em.

13:30.143 --> 13:32.145
Ten strippers,
actually.

13:32.186 --> 13:34.981
[disbelieving laugh]

13:34.981 --> 13:37.984
I think they prefer the term
"exotic dancer."

13:38.026 --> 13:39.986
I don't know,
what do you guys think?

13:39.986 --> 13:42.739
Well, I‐‐

13:42.780 --> 13:44.157
I think it's great the school
wants to recognize you.

13:44.198 --> 13:46.075
You know,
and the town too.

13:46.117 --> 13:47.744
You deserve this, Jason.

13:47.785 --> 13:50.872
Honestly,
I think it's too soon.

13:50.872 --> 13:52.373
Wait a second, now.
Hold on.

13:52.415 --> 13:53.875
We discussed this.

13:53.875 --> 13:56.335
No, Mitchell,
you discussed it.

13:56.335 --> 13:59.005
(Joanne)
It's barely been two months
since the accident.

13:59.047 --> 14:02.008
The sooner he can get back
to a normal routine, the better.

14:02.008 --> 14:03.843
You think this is normal?

14:03.843 --> 14:06.804
Trotting him out in front
of 15,000 people?

14:06.846 --> 14:08.806
Mom, let me think
about it, all right?

14:08.848 --> 14:10.516
Let's not do this here.

14:10.516 --> 14:12.310
Okay.

14:15.480 --> 14:16.981
[Riggins grunting]
Steady!

14:17.023 --> 14:18.274
Get it.

14:18.316 --> 14:20.860
[Riggins grunting]

14:20.860 --> 14:22.820
Riggins, you're gonna
give yourself a coronary.

14:22.862 --> 14:25.198
(McGill)
Williams!

14:25.198 --> 14:27.033
Smash.

14:27.033 --> 14:30.078
Smash,
come here.

14:31.537 --> 14:33.081
Grady Hunt left a message.

14:33.122 --> 14:34.540
Wants you to call him.

14:34.582 --> 14:35.917
(guy)
Uh‐oh.

14:35.917 --> 14:38.044
[cheers and catcalls]

14:38.044 --> 14:39.378
Tell him about me.

14:39.378 --> 14:40.379
Pucker up, Williams.

14:40.379 --> 14:41.881
That's right, baby,

14:41.923 --> 14:43.883
show me some love,
shoe me some love, baby!

14:43.925 --> 14:46.052
[laughter]

14:46.052 --> 14:47.887
Hey, look, this boy's going
to Austin.

14:47.887 --> 14:50.056
And don't worry, baby,
I'ma bring you back a T‐shirt.

14:50.056 --> 14:51.099
Longhorns.

14:54.936 --> 14:57.188
(Taylor)
How'd you end up
in Dallas?

14:57.230 --> 15:01.025
You know, I just
sorta did.

15:01.067 --> 15:02.902
Mm‐hmm.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.195
As good a place
as any.

15:04.237 --> 15:06.531
How big's the agency
up there?

15:09.283 --> 15:10.743
Can I tell you something?

15:10.785 --> 15:11.828
Sure.

15:11.869 --> 15:14.789
Keep it between us?
Uh‐huh.

15:14.831 --> 15:18.251
I don't have
an agency.

15:18.251 --> 15:20.086
I've just been
telling people that

15:20.086 --> 15:23.256
because I had to
tell 'em something.

15:23.256 --> 15:26.843
Sophomore year
I blew out my knee,

15:26.884 --> 15:27.927
which sucked.

15:27.927 --> 15:31.889
But I wasn't playing that much
as it was anyway.

15:31.931 --> 15:32.640
Met a girl.

15:32.682 --> 15:35.518
Pretty much lost focus
on football.

15:35.560 --> 15:40.439
Lost my scholarship,
pretty much dropped out.

15:40.481 --> 15:42.483
Never even graduated.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.821
I'm sorry to hear that.
I didn't know.

15:48.322 --> 15:51.534
Coach, listen.

15:51.576 --> 15:53.202
Let me ask you something.

15:53.244 --> 15:54.245
What's that?

15:54.287 --> 15:56.998
Could you hire me?

15:56.998 --> 15:58.958
I'm kinda putting you
on the spot.

15:59.000 --> 16:00.126
I don't‐‐I don't mean
to do that.

16:00.126 --> 16:01.460
I just‐‐

16:01.460 --> 16:02.461
[clears throat]

16:02.503 --> 16:04.797
I could log tapes,
I can scout.

16:04.839 --> 16:05.965
Carry the damn
water bottles.

16:06.007 --> 16:07.967
I understand.
I can look into it.

16:08.009 --> 16:11.804
I can't make any promises
to you, obviously, but I can...

16:11.846 --> 16:14.974
You know, I can look into it.
Certainly.

16:15.016 --> 16:16.630
That's something.
I appreciate that.

16:27.653 --> 16:30.072
Hey, babe.

16:30.114 --> 16:31.073
Hey.

16:31.115 --> 16:33.242
Did I wake you up?

16:33.284 --> 16:34.285
No.

16:34.327 --> 16:35.328
Did you sleep at all?

16:35.328 --> 16:38.331
Yeah, I got
a little bit.

16:38.372 --> 16:40.541
How was your dinner
with Lucas?

16:40.541 --> 16:42.168
Mmm...

16:42.168 --> 16:44.170
He asked for a job.

16:44.212 --> 16:46.297
He's got a job.

16:46.339 --> 16:47.506
He sells insurance
in Dallas.

16:47.506 --> 16:49.508
No, he doesn't have a job

16:49.508 --> 16:51.427
selling insurance
in Dallas.

16:51.469 --> 16:53.012
He never graduated college,

16:53.012 --> 16:54.263
and he's got
a four‐year‐old son

16:54.305 --> 16:56.265
that he hardly
ever sees,

16:56.307 --> 16:58.017
or he's never seen before,
I'm not sure which.

16:58.059 --> 16:59.185
That is the most
depressing thing

16:59.185 --> 17:00.853
I've ever heard.

17:00.895 --> 17:02.021
I'm not the kid's father.

17:02.021 --> 17:02.855
I don't know why
he's coming to me.

17:02.897 --> 17:04.941
Listen,
that is for sure.

17:04.982 --> 17:07.026
This is not your‐‐
I tutored him once,
for one season,

17:07.068 --> 17:09.320
six years ago.

17:09.362 --> 17:10.154
You know what the problem is,
it's this town, baby.

17:10.196 --> 17:12.156
This town makes
these teenage kids

17:12.198 --> 17:14.200
into idols.
He's a good kid.

17:14.200 --> 17:16.035
And then they get out
of here,

17:16.035 --> 17:17.203
and everybody's not just giving
'em something all the time.

17:17.203 --> 17:18.996
They don't know what
to do with themselves.

17:19.038 --> 17:19.997
They fall flat
on their faces.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.082
It's a shame.

17:21.082 --> 17:23.084
What are you
gonna do?

17:25.086 --> 17:27.213
He was the head trainer
for Villanova.

17:27.255 --> 17:28.506
You've seriously never
heard about this?

17:28.547 --> 17:29.507
No.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.133
See, you gotta remember,

17:31.175 --> 17:33.052
I wasn't even born
1985, old man.

17:33.052 --> 17:35.346
Well, the poor bastard had
Lou Gehrig's disease,

17:35.388 --> 17:36.138
and he was in a chair.

17:36.180 --> 17:38.891
And the whole season,
before games,

17:38.933 --> 17:40.476
they rolled him out
on the court.

17:40.518 --> 17:42.520
Then the team would
come out

17:42.562 --> 17:44.522
and rub his head
for good luck.

17:44.564 --> 17:45.565
[scoffs]

17:45.565 --> 17:47.358
It was sick, bro.

17:47.400 --> 17:49.569
What's wrong with it?
Sounds fine to me.

17:49.569 --> 17:51.696
Well, that's 'cause
you're an idiot.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.239
Why would you want to
let them make you into

17:53.239 --> 17:56.075
some pathetic mascot, huh?

17:56.075 --> 17:57.910
It's not a mascot, man.

17:57.952 --> 17:59.662
I'd be honored.
[cell phone rings]

17:59.704 --> 18:01.080
[thud]
Get that for me?

18:01.122 --> 18:02.290
Yes, sir.

18:02.290 --> 18:04.083
If you can move
fast enough.

18:04.125 --> 18:06.377
You should see me.
They call me greased lightning.

18:06.419 --> 18:10.089
Oh‐ho,
lovely Lyla.

18:10.131 --> 18:11.257
You can leave that.
That's fine.

18:11.257 --> 18:13.259
[chuckles]
Oh, okay.

18:13.259 --> 18:14.010
What?
I'm kinda busy.

18:14.051 --> 18:15.428
Strapped into a machine
right now.

18:15.428 --> 18:16.596
Don't wanna talk.

18:16.596 --> 18:18.598
Something's up.
I can smell it.

18:18.598 --> 18:20.099
Yeah, well, that's
none of your business.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.100
Oh, come on,
what'd you do?

18:21.100 --> 18:23.769
Miss an anniversary?

18:23.769 --> 18:26.105
Forgot to thank her for those
Rice Krispie balls, didn't you?

18:26.105 --> 18:28.441
No, I didn't do anything.

18:28.441 --> 18:31.611
Ah, so Little
Miss Perfect's the one

18:31.611 --> 18:33.029
that's in the doghouse.

18:33.070 --> 18:36.282
Interesting.
Oh.

18:36.282 --> 18:40.411
I'm all ears, QB.
The doctor is in.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.079
Come on.

18:44.624 --> 18:48.210
I, uh‐‐

18:48.252 --> 18:50.296
I kinda‐‐

18:50.296 --> 18:53.090
Kinda think she might be
sleeping with my best friend.

18:53.132 --> 18:55.301
Oh!
Oh, wow.

18:55.301 --> 18:57.303
But seriously,
I'm probably just paranoid.

18:57.345 --> 18:58.387
I mean, I've been
locked up‐‐

18:58.429 --> 18:59.639
I'm changing my mind.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.307
You gotta go
to that game now.

19:01.349 --> 19:03.309
You go look that son of a bitch
in the eye,

19:03.351 --> 19:05.144
and you see what is up.

19:05.144 --> 19:07.146
[Herc chuckling]

19:07.146 --> 19:09.482
(Tyra)
I don't know,
golf bores me.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.400
Yeah?

19:11.442 --> 19:13.319
Well, I was pretty damn good.

19:13.319 --> 19:14.445
I had three top tens on
the Hooters qualifying tour.

19:14.487 --> 19:17.114
And if it hadn't been
for September 11th,

19:17.156 --> 19:18.324
I probably would have
gotten my card.

19:18.324 --> 19:19.492
So, what, it's
the terrorists' fault?

19:19.533 --> 19:23.329
No, I'm not blaming
the terrorists.

19:23.329 --> 19:25.456
They cancelled
the Texas swing that year.

19:25.498 --> 19:26.457
Right when I was
on a roll.

19:26.499 --> 19:29.168
And then it's Christmastime.
My dad leaves us.

19:29.168 --> 19:31.420
And all of a sudden,
I got Tim living with me.

19:31.462 --> 19:32.672
It was, like,

19:32.713 --> 19:36.092
I don't know.
Adios, golf career.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.135
Hello, taking care
of your little brother.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.261
What about your mom?

19:39.303 --> 19:42.515
Well, she was a mess.

19:42.515 --> 19:47.019
She spent most of her time
sitting out on the back porch,

19:47.061 --> 19:48.437
sucking down
bourbon and Cokes,

19:48.479 --> 19:49.689
chain‐smoking
menthol lights.

19:49.730 --> 19:51.482
She was always screaming
about something.

19:51.524 --> 19:52.692
You know, in three years,

19:52.733 --> 19:54.777
she never once saw me
play football?

19:54.819 --> 19:57.113
Sorry.

19:57.154 --> 19:59.490
I don't usually whine.

19:59.532 --> 20:01.325
No, it's just‐‐

20:01.367 --> 20:02.702
It's just funny.

20:02.702 --> 20:04.370
I learned more about
the Riggins family

20:04.370 --> 20:07.415
in two minutes than I did
in a whole year of dating Tim.

20:07.415 --> 20:09.166
He doesn't talk much.

20:09.208 --> 20:10.376
No, ma'am.

20:10.418 --> 20:12.503
You're right about that.

20:12.545 --> 20:16.507
UT, Texas Tech,

20:16.549 --> 20:19.552
LSU, USC.

20:19.552 --> 20:21.470
Ohio State,

20:21.512 --> 20:24.140
I seem to be doing okay.

20:24.181 --> 20:25.391
Well, I'm sorry to tell you,
but any kid

20:25.433 --> 20:27.393
that can run 20 yards
without falling down

20:27.393 --> 20:28.477
gets one of those
his junior year.

20:28.519 --> 20:31.564
You need to get serious
about this, son.

20:31.564 --> 20:33.149
Treat it like a job.

20:33.190 --> 20:34.400
Oh, no, I got a plan.

20:34.400 --> 20:35.818
I'm gonna get
a scholarship,

20:35.860 --> 20:37.403
I'm gonna go to college,

20:37.403 --> 20:38.571
and when I turn pro,
buy my mama

20:38.571 --> 20:41.490
the biggest house
in Carr County.

20:41.532 --> 20:42.491
Sheila gets the Escalade,

20:42.533 --> 20:43.743
and little sis gets
a pony.

20:43.743 --> 20:45.745
Yeah, that's right, Brian.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.289
[laughter]

20:48.330 --> 20:50.458
As far as
the physical skills go,

20:50.499 --> 20:51.417
don't I got what it takes?

20:51.459 --> 20:54.253
From what I saw today,
it looks pretty good.

20:54.253 --> 20:56.338
It's hard to say yet
on strength and size,

20:56.380 --> 20:57.590
but if you'd be willing‐‐

20:57.590 --> 20:58.591
Oh, don't even worry
about that.

20:58.591 --> 21:00.259
People have been saying
I'm too small since J. V.

21:00.301 --> 21:02.344
Ask my mama.
She'll tell you.

21:02.386 --> 21:04.513
But I've been starting
ever since.

21:04.555 --> 21:06.682
It's not the size,
it's the heart.

21:06.724 --> 21:08.768
Well, I reckon that's
what this game's for.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.603
I'll be watching it.

21:10.603 --> 21:12.354
And you'll see...

21:12.396 --> 21:14.231
Smashball, baby.

21:14.273 --> 21:15.441
[laughter]

21:19.403 --> 21:20.571
Is there nowhere
we can go

21:20.613 --> 21:21.739
to get away
from Homecoming?

21:21.781 --> 21:23.199
I mean, so what?

21:23.240 --> 21:25.576
You've graduated,
now you're fat and old.

21:25.618 --> 21:27.286
(Landry)
There she is,
right there.

21:27.286 --> 21:30.623
I really wish you'd just
work with me, Romeo.

21:30.664 --> 21:31.957
I mean, come on.

21:31.999 --> 21:33.417
Just go forth,

21:33.459 --> 21:36.796
and multiply.

21:36.796 --> 21:39.799
[rock‐rap music]

21:39.799 --> 21:46.555
♪ ♪

21:46.597 --> 21:49.558
(Tyra)
So, what do you think?

21:49.600 --> 21:51.644
I don't know,
it just seems a little fancy.

21:51.644 --> 21:53.562
Shut up.
That's the whole point.

21:53.604 --> 21:55.564
To make it seem
all mysterious.

21:55.606 --> 21:56.649
I like 'em, okay?

21:56.649 --> 21:59.568
What kind of party
are you trying to throw here?

21:59.610 --> 22:01.237
It's gonna be a good one.

22:01.278 --> 22:02.988
[both laughing]

22:02.988 --> 22:05.324
Hey, look who it is.

22:05.366 --> 22:06.325
What's going on there,
Rocky?

22:06.367 --> 22:08.494
Look, it's the new
and improved Tim Riggins.

22:08.536 --> 22:10.287
Clean and sober for what?

22:10.329 --> 22:12.540
About 24 hours now, huh?

22:12.540 --> 22:13.958
What are you
doing here, Tyra?

22:13.999 --> 22:16.460
Nothing.
Sitting.

22:16.502 --> 22:19.880
Nan called
from the office.

22:21.465 --> 22:23.717
Said she hopes
you're feeling better.

22:24.844 --> 22:26.804
I took a sick day, Tim.

22:26.846 --> 22:29.515
It's not a big deal.

22:29.557 --> 22:31.517
Look, all we're doing is
planning a party, Tim.

22:31.559 --> 22:33.644
Not that it's
any of your business.

22:33.686 --> 22:35.354
We broke up, remember?

22:35.354 --> 22:36.689
I remember.

22:36.730 --> 22:39.400
Show him the flyer.

22:42.486 --> 22:43.863
Since when
you quit drinking?

22:43.863 --> 22:45.698
You know what?

22:45.698 --> 22:48.617
Keep your flyer.
You guys have fun.

22:50.035 --> 22:52.288
I think you should come.

22:52.329 --> 22:53.747
[Jason on phone]
I don't know.

22:53.747 --> 22:55.040
I still don't know
if I'm ready

22:55.082 --> 22:56.667
to face everybody yet.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.627
You know,
it's embarrassing,

22:58.669 --> 23:00.379
being the center
of attention and all.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.381
Like you're not used
to that?

23:02.381 --> 23:03.382
Well, for football, maybe.

23:03.382 --> 23:05.384
But not for being hurt.

23:05.426 --> 23:06.468
I mean, come on,
it's like,

23:06.510 --> 23:08.679
"Hey, everybody, come
check out the freak show.

23:08.721 --> 23:10.556
Don't feed the animals."

23:10.556 --> 23:13.392
It's not like that.

23:13.392 --> 23:17.646
People just want
to see you, you know?

23:17.688 --> 23:20.482
I want to see you.

23:20.524 --> 23:22.568
Is that right?

23:22.568 --> 23:24.570
Mm‐hmm.

23:24.570 --> 23:26.238
So what are you wearing?

23:26.280 --> 23:27.406
[Lyla giggles]

23:27.406 --> 23:29.074
Stop it.

23:29.074 --> 23:30.701
Come on, Kermit
or Miss Piggy?

23:30.743 --> 23:31.452
Oh, my God!

23:31.493 --> 23:33.412
That's eighth grade,
you dork.

23:33.454 --> 23:35.581
[laughter]

23:41.545 --> 23:43.672
I don't know, it's‐‐

23:43.714 --> 23:44.924
Sometimes I wake up
on Fridays,

23:44.965 --> 23:49.011
and I‐‐I go to grab
my letter jacket, you know?

23:50.763 --> 23:52.431
I'm sure it'll
make my dad happy

23:52.473 --> 23:53.766
if I go.

23:53.807 --> 23:56.435
He's only called up
a zillion times tonight,

23:56.435 --> 23:59.605
trying to convince me.

23:59.605 --> 24:05.778
And, uh...I guess...

24:05.778 --> 24:07.529
you want me to go too?

24:07.571 --> 24:10.950
I just told you I did.

24:10.950 --> 24:12.743
Why wouldn't I?

24:12.785 --> 24:15.371
All right.

24:15.412 --> 24:17.706
All right, I'll go.

24:20.334 --> 24:21.794
Okay.

24:21.835 --> 24:23.629
Good.

24:23.671 --> 24:26.966
Yeah.
It'll be fine.

24:27.007 --> 24:29.009
Everything will be fine.

24:33.472 --> 24:34.932
One or two tight ends during
the game today?

24:34.974 --> 24:35.975
Let's go two.
We gotta go two tights on them.

24:35.975 --> 24:37.643
Hey.
You wanted to see me?

24:37.643 --> 24:39.144
Yeah.

24:39.144 --> 24:41.146
Hey, guys, give me
a second, would you?

24:41.146 --> 24:43.232
Hey, how you doing, Luke?
Good.

24:43.273 --> 24:44.316
How's everything going?

24:44.358 --> 24:45.484
Good.
How are you doing?

24:45.484 --> 24:46.235
I'm doing fine.

24:46.276 --> 24:48.487
A little stressful
around here.

24:48.487 --> 24:50.906
Oh...

24:53.659 --> 24:56.328
Hey, listen...

24:56.328 --> 24:57.913
I can't hire you.
I'm sorry.

24:57.997 --> 25:00.624
The budget's tight,

25:00.666 --> 25:01.959
and, you know,
there's just no room

25:02.001 --> 25:03.252
for another assistant
right now.

25:03.293 --> 25:04.962
That's just
the way it is.

25:05.004 --> 25:07.631
Did you even ask?

25:07.673 --> 25:09.008
Yeah, I sure did ask.

25:09.008 --> 25:10.175
You know,
it's a process.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.969
You know,
a process is what it is.

25:12.011 --> 25:13.429
We're three games into
the season right now.

25:13.470 --> 25:15.014
We can't afford
another assistant.

25:15.014 --> 25:16.348
That's the fact
of the matter right there.

25:16.348 --> 25:18.350
You know, you go around
to another school.

25:18.350 --> 25:20.019
You ask around,
something comes up,

25:20.019 --> 25:21.687
I'm more than happy
to help out.

25:21.687 --> 25:22.938
Coach, listen,
I need this now.

25:22.980 --> 25:23.856
I understand that.

25:23.856 --> 25:25.357
If it was the beginning
of the season,

25:25.357 --> 25:26.942
it'd be a different story,
but it's not.

25:26.984 --> 25:28.193
That's just the situation.

25:28.193 --> 25:29.528
I'll keep my ears open
for you.

25:29.570 --> 25:31.530
I'll do what I can
for you.

25:31.530 --> 25:34.408
Yeah, don't hold your breath.

25:36.035 --> 25:38.037
Hey, I'm sorry I couldn't
do more for you.

25:52.051 --> 25:53.218
Good God, Tyra.

25:53.260 --> 25:55.012
We've gotta have
an open bar.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.221
Yeah, but don't you think
it's a little much?

25:56.263 --> 25:57.973
We already ordered
16 kegs.

25:58.015 --> 26:00.142
Actually, it was 22.

26:00.184 --> 26:01.894
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What?

26:01.935 --> 26:02.895
The worst thing
that could happen is that

26:02.936 --> 26:03.979
we run out of booze
in the middle of the party.

26:04.021 --> 26:06.023
We're not gonna have time
to come running back here.

26:06.065 --> 26:07.066
Yeah, I know, but‐‐

26:07.066 --> 26:08.734
So get with the program.

26:08.734 --> 26:09.735
If we want this thing
to be a hit,

26:09.735 --> 26:10.986
we gotta think big, okay?

26:11.028 --> 26:14.031
Just trust me on this.

26:29.421 --> 26:31.590
Hey.

26:31.590 --> 26:33.425
Whatcha doing?

26:33.467 --> 26:36.095
We got a game, Coach.

26:36.095 --> 26:39.098
I know, in about
four hours.

26:39.098 --> 26:42.226
Yeah, I'm just trying
to get my mind right, you know.

26:42.267 --> 26:43.393
Do my thing.

26:43.435 --> 26:45.437
All right.

26:47.981 --> 26:49.191
Hey, Coach?

26:49.233 --> 26:51.443
Hmm?

26:51.443 --> 26:53.112
What you know about
this Grady Hunt guy?

26:53.112 --> 26:55.405
Grady Hunt?
Grady Hunt?

26:55.447 --> 26:57.116
I know Grady Hunt has
a list of people

26:57.116 --> 26:58.450
like you on it
to look at.

26:58.492 --> 26:59.618
Why?

26:59.618 --> 27:03.163
Everybody says he has the power
to make or break you.

27:03.163 --> 27:05.999
He ain't no Jesus
or nothin', but...

27:06.041 --> 27:08.127
he's coming.

27:08.127 --> 27:09.711
It's just a lot,
that's all.

27:09.753 --> 27:12.172
Let me tell you something.
You're a prospect.

27:14.091 --> 27:15.425
There's gonna be
a lot of Grady Hunts

27:15.467 --> 27:16.802
coming in and out of here
the next few years,

27:16.802 --> 27:18.053
looking at you.

27:18.095 --> 27:20.639
You think so?
I know so.

27:20.681 --> 27:23.308
And I'll tell you
something else.

27:23.308 --> 27:26.311
Grady Hunt is not gonna
make or break number 20.

27:26.311 --> 27:27.312
You are.

27:27.354 --> 27:30.774
You go out there tonight,
you focus on this game.

27:30.816 --> 27:32.150
You focus on
this game alone.

27:32.150 --> 27:34.486
You'll be fine.
You understand me?

27:34.486 --> 27:36.154
Yes, sir.

27:36.154 --> 27:38.490
You're right.

27:42.160 --> 27:43.787
We're all good?

27:43.829 --> 27:45.539
Oh, yeah.
All right.

27:45.581 --> 27:48.208
All ready.
All right.

27:54.673 --> 27:58.093
[deep breath]

27:59.845 --> 28:02.806
All right, move these
over there, boys.

28:02.848 --> 28:04.141
Just set 'em‐‐
Unh!

28:04.182 --> 28:06.018
Don't hurt yourself.

28:06.059 --> 28:08.812
We got lots more to go.
All right?

28:08.854 --> 28:10.731
Yeah...

28:16.862 --> 28:18.780
[Sammy Meade on radio]
It is Homecoming, Panther fans,

28:18.822 --> 28:21.533
and have we got a good one
for you here tonight.

28:21.533 --> 28:23.368
(announcer #2)
Sammy, you can just feel
the electricity

28:23.410 --> 28:24.661
here in the football stadium.

28:24.703 --> 28:26.747
(Sammy)
And Laribee has taken
the field,

28:26.788 --> 28:29.374
and this crowd is rockin'

28:29.416 --> 28:31.710
as we wait for the Panthers.

28:31.710 --> 28:36.256
[cheering]

28:44.222 --> 28:46.391
[stadium announcer over P. A.]
And here are...

28:46.391 --> 28:47.643
your Dillon Panthers!

28:47.684 --> 28:50.729
[cheering]

29:01.365 --> 29:04.326
[heartfelt instrumental music]

29:04.368 --> 29:06.161
♪ ♪

29:06.203 --> 29:08.580
(stadium announcer)
Ladies and gentlemen,

29:08.622 --> 29:11.917
please welcome tonight's
honorary Dillon captain,

29:11.959 --> 29:16.546
number 6,
Jason Street!

29:16.588 --> 29:19.758
[crowd cheering wildly]

29:29.935 --> 29:33.230
[crowd chanting]
Jason! Jason!

29:38.610 --> 29:40.821
(players)
Let's go! Let's go, baby!

29:59.256 --> 30:01.800
[cheering]

30:01.800 --> 30:05.262
(team)
Clear eyes, full hearts,
can't lose!

30:05.303 --> 30:07.431
Clear eyes, full hearts,

30:07.472 --> 30:08.890
can't lose!

30:08.932 --> 30:10.183
[cheering]

30:25.532 --> 30:26.867
(Sammy)
Welcome back to tonight's
district match‐up.

30:26.908 --> 30:28.994
Dillon trying to get past
that forfeit to Arnett Mead

30:28.994 --> 30:31.288
because of
Ray "Voodoo" Tatom.

30:31.329 --> 30:32.330
And the Panthers
need a win

30:32.372 --> 30:34.374
to keep their playoff hopes
alive.

30:34.416 --> 30:35.709
And it's gonna be
a very emotional night

30:35.709 --> 30:38.503
with the return of
Jason Street

30:38.503 --> 30:39.629
to Herrmann Field.

30:39.671 --> 30:42.674
And word is out Grady Hunt
is in the house

30:42.716 --> 30:44.509
to see Smash Williams
do his thing.

30:44.551 --> 30:46.511
All right, let's go,
lock and load, let's play ball!

30:46.511 --> 30:49.306
(Sammy)
Keller opens left,
reverses field.

30:49.347 --> 30:51.683
It's an option, he pitches.
No, he keeps it!

30:51.683 --> 30:53.685
This kid has got
some wheels.

30:53.685 --> 30:55.896
Oh, and a big gain
for the Laribee quarterback.

30:59.900 --> 31:01.860
He's got room.
He's hit hard at the line.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.362
Oh, and he's in
for a touchdown.

31:04.362 --> 31:05.864
(announcer #2)
Just like that, Coach Taylor's
gonna find himself

31:05.864 --> 31:08.283
down seven points.

31:08.325 --> 31:09.701
[cheering]

31:09.701 --> 31:11.703
Come on, show us
some of that speed, Smash.

31:11.745 --> 31:13.413
(Saracen)
I‐right, Y flip‐28 zone.

31:13.413 --> 31:14.915
On one.
Ready, break.

31:14.915 --> 31:15.916
(Sammy)
Okay, Panther fans,

31:15.916 --> 31:17.959
let's see
what Smash has brought.

31:18.001 --> 31:19.711
Saracen takes the snap,
hands the ball off

31:19.753 --> 31:20.879
to Williams
on the right side.

31:20.879 --> 31:22.798
He turns the corner‐‐

31:22.839 --> 31:24.633
Oh, and he gets pasted.

31:24.674 --> 31:26.718
Saracen's got Williams open
on the left flank‐‐

31:26.718 --> 31:28.845
Oh, and he just plumb drops
the ball.

31:28.887 --> 31:31.515
I'll tell you what, he had
nothing but blue skies

31:31.556 --> 31:35.393
and open fields between him
and the end zone.

31:35.393 --> 31:38.396
Riggins gets the ball,
and he powers up the middle

31:38.396 --> 31:39.397
for six yards.

31:39.439 --> 31:41.566
Late in the second quarter,
Panthers

31:41.608 --> 31:43.568
with a fourth and one
on their own 45.

31:43.568 --> 31:45.821
Saracen hands the ball off
to Dolia.

31:45.862 --> 31:49.908
Wait, it's a reverse
to Smash Williams!

31:49.950 --> 31:54.412
Smash Williams just can't seem
to get on track tonight.

31:54.454 --> 31:57.749
(announcer #2)
This Panther team has been
shut out in the first half.

31:57.791 --> 31:59.751
Coach Taylor
needs to circle the wagons

31:59.793 --> 32:00.919
and find some answers fast,

32:00.961 --> 32:02.045
'cause this is gonna
turn into a massacre.

32:02.087 --> 32:04.047
(assistant coach)
You guys gotta wait

32:04.089 --> 32:05.841
on making those reads!

32:05.882 --> 32:09.427
[coaches shouting]

32:09.469 --> 32:11.972
(Taylor)
Let's go, right now.

32:16.476 --> 32:18.937
We're losing out there.
What the hell's going on?!

32:18.937 --> 32:19.938
Coach, look, they're not
holding their blocks.

32:19.938 --> 32:20.772
I can't get around 'em.

32:20.814 --> 32:22.774
You are running into
your own protection.

32:22.774 --> 32:23.692
The holes are open.

32:23.733 --> 32:26.111
Why are you running into
your own protection?

32:26.111 --> 32:28.405
Why aren't you being patient?
Read the blocks, hit the gaps.

32:28.446 --> 32:30.407
Read the blocks,
hit the gaps.

32:30.448 --> 32:32.075
Yes, sir.

32:32.117 --> 32:32.951
The problem is‐‐

32:32.951 --> 32:34.870
I'll tell you what
the problem is, Smash.

32:34.911 --> 32:36.746
The problem is the guy out there
with the damn clipboard.

32:36.788 --> 32:37.789
That's the problem.

32:37.831 --> 32:38.915
That's the problem.

32:38.957 --> 32:39.875
You don't play for UT.

32:39.916 --> 32:41.877
You play Dillon Panther
high school football.

32:41.918 --> 32:44.796
And you play for me.
So forget the damn list!

32:44.796 --> 32:46.590
I'm gonna
make it up to you.

32:46.631 --> 32:47.924
Yes, you are!

32:47.966 --> 32:48.967
'Cause if you don't,
I'm gonna make

32:48.967 --> 32:49.968
some changes out there.

32:50.010 --> 32:51.011
I promise you that!

32:55.640 --> 32:56.975
(Sammy)
Starting the second half here,

32:56.975 --> 33:00.145
and these Panther fans without
a whole lot to celebrate

33:00.145 --> 33:01.980
on Homecoming so far.

33:02.022 --> 33:04.399
Down ten points, we're gonna
see how many touches

33:04.441 --> 33:05.984
Smash Williams'll get.

33:06.026 --> 33:08.028
[whistle blows]

33:10.822 --> 33:11.948
He takes the snap.

33:13.658 --> 33:15.076
Oh, Williams
gets hit hard again.

33:15.118 --> 33:16.912
And the ball's loose!
Fumble!

33:16.953 --> 33:18.705
Oh, and Laribee's
picking it up.

33:21.041 --> 33:23.084
What are you doing?

33:23.126 --> 33:25.003
(Sammy)
They are not gonna catch him,
and that is a touchdown

33:25.003 --> 33:26.004
for the Laribee Lions.

33:26.046 --> 33:27.172
And just like that, folks,

33:27.172 --> 33:29.007
the Panthers are down

33:29.007 --> 33:32.010
here in the third quarter,
17 to nothing.

33:32.010 --> 33:33.011
(announcer #2)
I don't know what's wrong.

33:33.053 --> 33:34.137
This team is just struggling
tonight.

33:34.179 --> 33:36.973
They continue to be
out of synch‐‐Oh!

33:37.015 --> 33:39.017
And Smash Williams has just
thrown his helmet

33:39.017 --> 33:40.101
to the ground
in frustration.

33:40.143 --> 33:42.646
[crowd booing]

33:42.687 --> 33:45.482
That's it,
we're going with Riggins.

33:45.523 --> 33:46.942
I‐right, 42 swing pass,
on one.

33:46.983 --> 33:48.068
Ready, break!

33:50.070 --> 33:51.655
(Sammy)
And Coach Taylor
has Tim Riggins

33:51.696 --> 33:53.782
lined up
as the lone tailback.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.035
And the ball is given
to Riggins.

33:57.035 --> 33:59.913
And he picks up
a quick ten yards.

34:01.039 --> 34:02.999
Riggins again up the middle.

34:03.041 --> 34:07.045
And he bulldozes his way in,
and it's a touchdown!

34:07.045 --> 34:09.422
[cheering]

34:11.049 --> 34:13.969
And with Riggins as the new
go‐to workhorse tonight,

34:14.010 --> 34:16.054
Dillon can't be stopped.

34:16.054 --> 34:17.472
Get 'em!

34:17.514 --> 34:18.682
I'm on you.
Let's go!

34:18.723 --> 34:20.892
(Sammy)
Handoff to Riggins.

34:27.899 --> 34:29.901
Touchdown!
Touchdown, Dillon Panthers!

34:29.901 --> 34:32.821
[cheering]

34:34.197 --> 34:36.825
And Taylor may have finally
found his answer

34:36.866 --> 34:40.787
in the power running
of big Tim Riggins.

34:43.123 --> 34:45.125
Go, come on!

34:45.166 --> 34:47.794
(Sammy)
Riggins picks up
a good block.

34:56.219 --> 34:58.096
That is a touchdown!

34:58.096 --> 35:00.181
Touchdown, Dillon Panthers.

35:00.223 --> 35:03.184
[cheering]

35:09.274 --> 35:11.109
Way to play,
Riggins.

35:11.151 --> 35:14.112
[melancholy music]

35:14.154 --> 35:20.910
♪ ♪

35:20.952 --> 35:24.956
[players cheering]

35:29.294 --> 35:33.131
All right, listen up!

35:33.173 --> 35:35.133
Listen, now.

35:35.133 --> 35:38.136
Y'all ought to be
real proud of yourselves.

35:38.136 --> 35:40.055
That was a hell
of an effort tonight.

35:40.096 --> 35:41.806
It was a hell of a game.

35:41.848 --> 35:44.893
I don't know how in the hell
he did it,

35:44.934 --> 35:47.479
or where he came from
to do it, or what have you,

35:47.520 --> 35:49.981
but I know who
this game ball goes to.

35:49.981 --> 35:52.233
[cheering]

35:55.987 --> 35:58.114
Thank you.

35:58.156 --> 35:59.491
[cheering quiets]

35:59.532 --> 36:01.117
That was one hell
of a game.

36:01.159 --> 36:02.994
Thanks.
All of y'all.

36:02.994 --> 36:04.829
That was one hell
of a game!

36:04.829 --> 36:07.791
[cheering]

36:09.209 --> 36:11.628
Speech, come on!
Panther pride!

36:11.670 --> 36:13.004
Speech!

36:13.004 --> 36:14.673
Well...

36:14.673 --> 36:15.757
I, uh...

36:17.133 --> 36:20.261
I'm not very good
at this kind of stuff, so...

36:20.303 --> 36:23.848
Coach is always talking
about, uh...

36:23.890 --> 36:25.975
one team and one heart.

36:27.227 --> 36:29.187
To be honest with you,
I thought it was‐‐

36:29.229 --> 36:32.982
I thought it was stupid.

36:33.024 --> 36:35.610
Fact is, he's right.

36:35.652 --> 36:37.195
He's right.

36:37.195 --> 36:40.990
Everybody in this room
knows who...

36:43.910 --> 36:46.371
where we get our heart from.

36:46.371 --> 36:49.666
He's sitting right there.

36:52.168 --> 36:54.713
This ball belongs to you.

36:59.259 --> 37:02.929
[quietly]
Please, take it.

37:08.727 --> 37:10.145
(Riggins
I love you like a brother.

37:12.897 --> 37:14.357
Like a brother, Six.

37:21.239 --> 37:22.115
What are y'all staring at?

37:22.157 --> 37:24.075
Y'all played a hell of a game.
Go party!

37:24.075 --> 37:25.994
[cheering]

37:45.430 --> 37:47.265
Well, don't you say
one word to your brother.

37:47.307 --> 37:49.934
Not one word.
Just wait here.

37:49.934 --> 37:52.604
Baby, it's okay.
It's just one game.

37:52.645 --> 37:54.355
I blew it.
I blew it.

37:54.397 --> 37:55.940
I had my one chance,
and I blew it.

37:55.982 --> 37:58.777
I didn't even touch the ball
the second half of the game.

37:58.777 --> 38:00.945
Everybody know that I'm
this family's meal ticket.

38:00.987 --> 38:02.113
Now, that's crazy talk.

38:02.113 --> 38:03.406
You know better
than that.

38:03.448 --> 38:05.950
You know it.
I know it.

38:05.950 --> 38:07.786
And this whole
damn world knows it.

38:07.827 --> 38:11.748
Look, I'm sorry.

38:11.790 --> 38:13.666
I just‐‐
I need to be alone.

38:13.708 --> 38:14.667
Brian. Brian!

38:16.461 --> 38:19.798
[loud dance music playing]

38:29.808 --> 38:31.392
Little brother,
what is up, man?

38:31.434 --> 38:32.727
Hell of a game tonight, man!

38:32.769 --> 38:34.229
Thank you.

38:42.320 --> 38:45.073
Why don't you come back
in about four years?

38:45.114 --> 38:46.324
I'll give you one
on the house.

38:46.324 --> 38:48.827
Think maybe I can
get that in writing?

38:48.827 --> 38:49.828
You're cute.

38:49.828 --> 38:51.704
I'm cute?

38:53.540 --> 38:55.416
[knocking on door]

38:59.504 --> 39:01.756
I gotta be up early, son.

39:01.798 --> 39:03.758
I'm sorry, sir.
I don't mean to bother you.

39:03.800 --> 39:06.427
But I was just wondering
if there's any chance

39:06.469 --> 39:07.971
I'm gonna make that list.

39:09.806 --> 39:11.099
You had a rough time
out there tonight.

39:11.140 --> 39:13.101
Yes, sir, I did.

39:13.142 --> 39:15.353
But I didn't get
my touches, and‐‐

39:15.353 --> 39:17.355
They don't want
to hear excuses.

39:17.397 --> 39:19.774
No, sir.

39:19.816 --> 39:23.194
To be honest, I'm worried
about your strength and size.

39:23.194 --> 39:28.157
So what you should work on
is lifting and conditioning.

39:28.199 --> 39:29.534
Yes, sir.

39:29.534 --> 39:30.702
I appreciate that.

39:30.743 --> 39:31.786
I'm gonna keep on
pushing,

39:31.828 --> 39:34.873
but I was just wondering
if I'm gonna make that list.

39:34.914 --> 39:37.083
Comes out in January.

39:37.125 --> 39:39.252
Thank you.

39:41.421 --> 39:44.382
[dance music]

39:44.382 --> 39:46.968
♪ ♪

39:47.010 --> 39:48.720
It's gonna be
20 bucks a pop.

39:48.761 --> 39:51.014
Man, these people are
wearing my ass down.

39:51.055 --> 39:52.056
It's all the Red Bull
and vodka.

39:52.056 --> 39:53.224
They're either gonna
pass out,

39:53.224 --> 39:55.059
or run the marathon.

39:55.101 --> 39:57.770
Come on.

40:00.231 --> 40:01.482
Hey.

40:01.524 --> 40:04.360
Hey, what's goin' on?

40:04.402 --> 40:06.863
Not much.
Is this the safe zone?

40:06.905 --> 40:09.324
Yeah, I know.
These people are crazy.

40:14.412 --> 40:15.955
So, it must feel
pretty good,

40:15.955 --> 40:18.958
winning the big
homecoming game and all.

40:21.419 --> 40:24.339
Would you go on a date
with me?

40:26.424 --> 40:27.425
Um...

40:27.425 --> 40:28.843
Maybe, or not.
I mean‐‐

40:30.595 --> 40:34.098
I just thought
I'd throw that out there.

40:34.140 --> 40:36.559
But it's prob‐‐
It's probably a bad idea.

40:53.076 --> 40:56.037
[lighthearted country music]

40:56.079 --> 41:03.211
♪ ♪

41:03.252 --> 41:09.133
♪ ♪

41:12.637 --> 41:14.472
[chuckles]

41:14.472 --> 41:16.140
So, how'd we do?

41:16.140 --> 41:19.978
60, 70, 80.

41:19.978 --> 41:22.647
$4,680.

41:22.647 --> 41:25.817
Which comes out to...

41:25.858 --> 41:28.820
A whole lot of damn money
for throwing a stupid party.

41:28.861 --> 41:29.821
Yeah.

41:29.862 --> 41:30.989
This is unbelievable.

41:30.989 --> 41:33.408
So let me ask you
a question.

41:33.449 --> 41:35.952
How do I know you didn't pocket
a little bit of extra cash

41:35.994 --> 41:37.662
when you were lettin' people in
through the door?

41:37.662 --> 41:40.039
The same way I know you're
gonna share those tips

41:40.039 --> 41:41.457
you made at the bar with me.

41:41.499 --> 41:42.917
Trust.

41:49.465 --> 41:50.466
Wow.

41:54.012 --> 41:56.431
Nice.

41:56.472 --> 41:58.891
[laughter]

42:18.661 --> 42:19.954
[knock on door]

42:19.996 --> 42:22.582
(Corrina)
Come on, baby,
you got game film.

42:22.623 --> 42:24.959
I'm coming.

42:29.714 --> 42:32.925
[breathing heavily]
